# Styles and UI

## Summary

Defines styling patterns with Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui + Radix UI components, and animations with Framer Motion. Uses semantic color tokens and utility classes. Reference [nextjs](mdc:.cursor/rules/nextjs.mdc) for component conventions, [data-validation](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-validation.mdc) for prop types, and [security](mdc:.cursor/rules/security.mdc) for secure SVG handling.

## shadcn/ui + Radix UI

We use shadcn/ui. Base components are in `components/ui/`:

```tsx
// ✅ DO: Use components from ui/
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Dialog, DialogContent } from "@/components/ui/dialog";

<Button variant="destructive" size="sm">
  Cancel
</Button>;

// ❌ DON'T: Create custom buttons without using the system
<button className="bg-red-500 px-4 py-2">Cancel</button>;
```

### Available Button variants

- `default` | `destructive` | `outline` | `secondary` | `tertiary` | `ghost` | `link`
- Sizes: `default` | `sm` | `lg` | `icon`

## `cn()` utility for conditional classes

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<div
  className={cn(
    "base-classes",
    isActive && "active-classes",
    className, // allows override from props
  )}
/>;
```

## Theme colors

We use HSL CSS variables defined in `globals.css`. Always reference semantic tokens:

```tsx
// ✅ DO: Use semantic tokens
className = "bg-background text-foreground";
className = "bg-primary text-primary-foreground";
className = "text-muted-foreground";
className = "border-border";

// ❌ DON'T: Hardcoded colors
className = "bg-white text-black";
className = "bg-[#1a1a1a]";
```

## Animations with Framer Motion

```tsx
import { motion } from "framer-motion";

// Basic fade-in pattern
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
></motion.div>;

// For lists, use staggerChildren
const container = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  show: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1 },
  },
};
```

## Predefined CSS animations

The project has keyframes in `tailwind.config.js`:

- `animate-fade-up` - Fade from bottom
- `animate-fade-down` - Fade from top
- `animate-fade-in` - Simple fade

